- Implement media request system
    - Allow users to search for media through the discover endpoint
        - When the user selects a piece of media, it should check the database to see if it is already there.
            - If the media is already there, it will say that and list where (and what seasons are available, if it is a tv show). It will then ask if the user wants to request a different resolution
            - In the case of a tv show it should also allow to select seasons of a TV show to request
        - Users can then choose to submit a request with an optional resolution
        - This could be new media or something like a specific season of an existing tv show or something
        - should I just replace the library endpoint with discover?
    - Send a ping to server owners who are opted in
    - Check for media request fulfillment after every sync
        - If a users media request is fulfilled, close the request and send a ping to the user telling them the media is available to watch + on what server

- Ask RTP to set up pings
